lot that zips at breathtaking speed."--Kathy Reichs. "The Driver is grim, funny, violent, and moving--all on the same page."--T. Jefferson Parker"--cProvided by publisher. 0aChauffeursvFiction. 0aLimousine servicesvFiction. 0aDisabled veteransvFiction. 0aExtrasensory perceptionvFiction. 0aCelebritiesvFiction. 0aAttempted murdervFiction. 0aLos Angeles (Calif.)vFiction. 0aLarge type books. 7aFICTION / Suspense.2bisacsh 7aFICTION / Thrillers.2bisacsh 7aSuspense fiction.2gsafd 7aMystery fiction.2gsafd  c(OCoLC)0999671749